JOHANNESBURG - Former KPMG Africa CEO, Moses Kgosana, has refuted claims a Gupta family wedding was funded by taxpayer money.Kgosana resigned yesterday from his position as a non-executive director at Alexander Forbes following the allegations.WATCH: Zwane denies knowledge of Gupta's dairy project pay-offHe was due to become chairperson of Alexander Forbes next month.Kgosana was chief executive and senior partner at audit firm KPMG when the Gupta family organised a R30 million wedding at Sun City in 2013.New information from leaked Gupta emails suggest the wedding was funded by taxpayer money diverted from a Free State farming project.eNCA